description:
Strange Bedfellows

Trevor and Olive Armstrong are guns on the run, pursued by the relentless bounty hunter Portmanteaux in a warp powered chase across the country, as they make their way to a Nevada safe house that doubles as a brothel for super-powered clientele...

"Do you have a combustible body? Electro Touch? Periodically phase into a block of ice? For these demands a more calibrated class of escort is required and you find them at the Mermaid Lagoon..."
name: Strange Bedfellows

description:
Dead Ends

THE SECOND RIVETING ISSUE OF THE 8 PART SCI-FI GRAPHIC NOVEL

Z's got a problem - his last bounty was all wrong. On top of him dying (again), nothing about the mission made sense. Seeking out the one who ordered the bounty, Z lands on Yuganor, an overpopulated hive of corruption, a place Z really doesn't want to be. Unfortunately, the closer he gets to the one who ordered the bounty, the more things aren't what they seem. Something is going on and Z is determined to find out what.
name: Dead Ends

description: In this corner, fighting for aid in his journey to Queensbury: Mammoth! In the other corner, the Gateway Champion, determined to keep Mammoth's crew from heading west: Argos Dane! It's champion vs former champion for the fate of the quest...but will Mammoth throw the bout in order to get everything he's ever wanted since escaping Gaol? Ding, ding, kids. Grab a ringside seat for the fight of the...well, the fight of this issue, anyway.
The third issue of the Knights series!

Budget Issues

While their first trade was successful, Mike's shady dealings are still causing problems for the company. And they're starting to catch up with him.
name: Budget Issues

description:
Megalopolis Cracks!

ThinkTank unleashes Electrolyte's powers on Megalopolis to devastating results.
name: Megalopolis Cracks!

volume.name: The Misadventures of Electrolyte and The Justice Purveyors

description: Questions answered and the conflict thirty years in the making comes to a head!

In this fun-packed issue, Rose visits Egypt, ruins a date, suffers a devastating injury and tries to play football - and eats way too much in between. Just another day for a girl who is trying her best never to grow up!

The Old New, Part 2

Jara Bint Rih got injured during World War 3 and spent the last three years of her life in search of a suit she hoped would restore her ability to walk. She and her best friend Lucia Mason found the suit when they were attacked by a gang. But Jara managed to fend the gang off by using the suit. While out on patrol Shade got attacked by a masked vigilante who was faster and stronger than her and was able to know her every move before she made it. He knocked her out and took her to an old acquaintance of hers...
name: The Old New, Part 2

description: "The double-edged sword is by its design a threat to all once blood is first tasted. That which covets and is coveted presents no foundation for truth in any form." Shepherd 9:5-6

Hard Time

Treasure hunter Vivian Von Valiant is called to the Cedar Lake Correctional Institute where she seeks answers about something that has gone wrong with time and space. Featuring guest writer Brian Augustyn (THE FLASH, GOTHAM BY GASLIGHT) and artist John Derrick West (IMAGINARY DRUGS).
name: Chapter 6: Hard Time

description: The final hour has arrived as Virgin and Hania face off against the Father of All Wolfen while The Crimson Mask races across the countryside in an attempt to stop a religious war that could span all across France before hitting the shores of England, and even that of the New World.

Cycles

The Plateau opens up its spring market despite concerns about an Outlander invasion. Redlabs tries to find a cure for the feeder scourge while Hochelaga looks for answers about a missing comrade on the Mountain.
name: Cycles

description:
A Bleak Christmas

It's Christmas Eve 1908 in New York City, and Joe has a visitor who offers him a precious gift... only he may have to risk life and limb to accept it!
name: A Bleak Christmas

description: A mentally challenged man accidentally takes on the members of a local crime syndicate after they hurt his best friend... a little pug.

A Matter of Life and Deather

Colonel MacTaggart and February are on the hunt for the dangerous beast known as the Serrapoh.
name: A Matter of Life and Deather

description: As a member of the most elite of these soldiers, the Aesir, Owen is sent on a journey back to Earth to set up an outpost. However, all does not go according to plan. When Owen awakes, he is where he set out to be but not when. What comes after he opens his eyes, not only changes his life but changes that course of the future itself.

A notorious train robber has been caught and sentenced to death by hanging and the whole town comes out to witness the execution of the most wanted man in three states.

On the gallows, the man tells anyone who will listen that his loot is buried and he will give the location to anyone who helps spare his life.

The townsfolk are poor..... His old gang wants the money...... And the town sheriff is left with just two choices....

HANG LOW or AIM HIGH

Beautiful art done in watercolors to give an authentic western feel to the book!

I Am No One

Six years ago, little Katherine Harlow killed her own parents. Showing no signs of remorse or regret, she was said to be a girl without a soul. Now, dressed in black except for an expressionless white mask, Kat kills for the dead - a willing vessel for the souls of the wrongfully killed that call out for vengeance.

But how did an apparently soulless child become a brutal vigilante? And are the voices that she hears really those of the dead or are they merely symptoms of a dangerous, all-consuming psychosis?
name: I Am No One

description: England, 1919. Disfigured Great War veteran Tarquin Price and his friends escape from The Royal Jericho Hospital, a dumping ground for the disabled and insane.
A young Buddhist monk must defeat luchador demons and resist the thrall of an enchanted dagger in order to reclaim her own destiny and end a cycle of violence that stretches across lifetimes!

Theres a dangerous website where women get to explore their true passions. My Dog House is making rounds online, but many of the visitors end up missing. If found, theyve been brought to levels of depravity unheard of by society. What is this sites connection to the mysterious Breeder, and how is he connected to this girl, Alice, who may harbor the secret to eternal life and health? Is she the mutt at the end of a yanked chain, or is she the tail wagging the dog?
name: Vol. 1

description:
The Vial

Piet is captured during a desperate escape to protect the vial and solve the chronic problem of water scarcity. She is sentenced to death alongside a treacherous thief. To free her, a mysterious warrior arises; someone who seems to be much more than a mere mercenary...
name: The Vial

description: Andres Sanchez sees demons. Literally. When he looks into a person's eyes, he can see whether or not they are truly demonic in nature. Hired to find and assassinate a known child trafficker, Sanchez goes on the hunt, taking out demons as he perceives while getting closer to his target. But can Sanchez truly trust what he sees?
A troll, faun and dragon are on the run from the United States government in this geopolitical fantasy from creators Paul Allor and Louie Joyce.

Cartoonist Tom Bouden (Max and Sven, The Importance of Being Earnest) invites you to meet Sarah, a young woman whose life is about to be turned inside out when she discovers that's she's HIV positive.

Join Sarah and her partner, Tim, as they take the journey together through shock and uncertainty, pre-dawn pill schedules, side-effects, well-meaning friends, tasteless jokes, medical missteps, and ultimately, hope.

Manuel's mother opened an ecological hotel on the outskirts of Darwin, where all the family moved too. Amongst the guests, Dr. Fast stands out, a scientist who has designed a solar driven car and who took it upon himself to compete in an extraordinary race. But Fast's desire to compete was for ever being undermined by the constant attempts at sabotage of a pair of wrong doers. On the other hand, there will be new play mates and games for Manuel arriving at the hotel, to accompany him at this stage of his life, in which he is developing a deep ecological conscience.

A disgruntled high school student takes revenge on her senior, and through a strange application on her phone; turns into the deadly Speedster Meerkat.

However, she is interrupted by a hero donning a Red Belt.
Evil has a new name and it is one that can not be stopped! He is out to destroy all superheroes and his name is SADISTIC!

Two businessmen and three college co-eds stranded in the southern backwoods try to survive in a town of misfits and a hulking slasher.

Can any of them make it back to civilization alive? Or will they be picked off one-by-one before realizing a worse threat is closer than they ever imagined?
name: Vol. 1

description:
Timothy is a regular guy, with an extra regular day job of pushing drive thru burgers. One night, just after getting off work, he wanders downtown to relieve his service stress.

When he encounters a mysterious new night club titled "Club Oblivion", he unwittingly enters into a portal of an unseen netherworld.

He soon confronts a black abyss of demons as he wanders through doorways of extra dimensional deception. Will he make it through this ever changing realm of confusion back into the light of day?

Perhaps an answer lies in his confrontation with the dark specter doorman who led him here.

Timothy the Tortured One is brand new supernatural comedy created by Ethan Wenberg (The Grubbie Wubbies).

Un-redressed Grievances

Lost in the depths of time and space, Dr. Kevin Sheck and his murderous uncle find themselves facing off in a duel to the death upon first arriving to the fantasy world Urde.
name: Un-redressed Grievances

description: Watson and Holmes returns in 4 standalone stories! Volume 2 has Eisner nominated and Glyph winning issue #6 written by Brandon Easton with art by N.Steven Harris. Includes new reinterpretation of 2 classic Sherlock Holmes stories, including Irene Adler by Lyndsay Faye. Other creators include- Steven Grant, Hannibal Tabu, Dennis Calero, Karl Bollers, and Eli Powell.
name: Volume 2

description:
Coked Out Demon Worshippers

Weird Luck opens with a single issue horror-comedy, "Coked Out Demon Worshippers." Here we see Akaz, the Demon-Wolf of Kaios - a major player in the ongoing Weird Luck series - dealing with a couple of jerks who think they can just drag him to Earth and make him do stuff. Also included is the oddball short story "Water Damage." Written by Andrew M. Reichart & Illustrated by Mike Bennewitz.
name: Coked Out Demon Worshippers; Water Damage

description: It was written in blood by the rat kings, woven in silk by the spider sages, recited in verse by the ancient warlords of the centipedes. The Vermin shall inherit the Earth.

Reopen the files on the ultimate conspiracy theory. Join Agents Mulder and Scully in their epic quest to expose the truth, and meet the shadowy players intent on concealing it at all costs. From the corridors of the FBI to the highest level of government The truth is out there, and it wants to be known.

Behind the scenes secrets revealed!

In-depth features investigating the mythology of the show!

Exclusive interviews with the stars of The X-Files!

Material previously published in Titan Magazines official The X-Files Magazine.
name: The Agents, The Bureau, and The Syndicate

description:
JEZUS

Born in a stable as the son of a carpenter and virgin, yet destined one day to become the leader of an entire generation. This was something nobody would ever have predicted of baby Jezus. However, thanks to clever marketing and effective PR stunts Jezus was quickly able to attract hordes of believers to his cause,

most notably those who made up his crew - the twelve Disciples. This is the story of one of them: Judaz, allegedly the traitor. Here he gives us his view of things. Based on what was said at the time and only recently discovered, his account forms the second part of the Gospel according to Judaz.

The story of Zombie-ism now has to be rewritten.

Krack-A-Thoom!! Zomkeys is a project born out of a lifetime of reading comics and watching movies. Many of which weren't of the highest calibre, but none-the-less were near and dear to the writers heart. It's a pulp sci-fi horror story that would have been seen in a grindhouse theatre or a drive-in in the 1970's, without any special effects or budgetary limitations. Zomkeys is part beware the power of nature theme from Jurassic Park, mixed with exaggerated horrors of the deceased seen in films like Night of the Living Dead. It's over-the-top comic book adventure with scary monsters, shadowy villains, and Hollywood movie style action and explosions; true B-Movie Horror fun.
